 Purpose

This workflow will provision a pluggable database(PDB) within an Oracle Container Database(CDB)\:


 Dependencies

    -- The workflow will need to have an Oracle Container Database (CDB) already provisioned as your target instance.

 Results Verification

The Console will indicate whether the workflow completed without errors. If all required services are online then your installation was successful.

To further verify the results\:

 1. Set ORACLE_HOME and ORACLE_SID in the terminal(s) for your PDB instance.
 2. sqlplus admin/admin_password@PDB
 3. If login is successful your PDB has been created successfully.



 Additional Documentation

Additional information about HP Database and Middleware Automation is available on HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the OTHER FILES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
 Required Inputs

    Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
    Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
    Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
    Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
    Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
    Instance.Instance Name - No description
    Instance.Oracle Home - No description
    Pluggable Database Name - Required\: Name of the pluggable database to be created in the container database.

 Optional Inputs

    Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
    Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
    Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
    Download Location - No description
    Admin User Password - Optional\: Password for the Admin User for pluggable database. This is required if you are creating a new pluggable from scatch.
    Instance.OS User - No description
    Source Clone Database - Optional\: Source pluggable database name if cloning pluggable database from an exsiting pluggable database.
    Admin User - Optional\: Main user for the pluggable database
    Pluggable XML Source - Optional\: XML file containing the pluggable database you want to plug-in .
    Storage Max Size - Optional\: Max size the pluggable database will be allowed to grow. Format\:  Example\: 2G
    Default Tablespace - Optional\: Tablespace pluggable database will default to. If not specified it will default to Oracle's defaults.
    Cleanup On Success - No description
    Cleanup On Failure - No description
